---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { PROFILE } from '../data/profile';
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="Pete Ghiorse builds AI products, runs production experiments, and writes about what the evidence changes.">
  <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-16 md:py-24">
    <p class="text-(--color-primary) font-semibold text-sm tracking-widest uppercase mb-4 animate-fade-up">About</p>
    <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-extrabold mb-10 animate-fade-up stagger-1">
      What I build, what I test, and <span class="gradient-text">why I write</span>
    </h1>

    <div class="space-y-6 text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400 leading-relaxed animate-fade-up stagger-2">
      <p class="text-lg">
        I work at the point where AI leaves the demo and meets someone's actual day.
      </p>

      <p>
        I split my time between two roles: <strong class="text-slate-900 dark:text-white font-semibold">Group Product Manager</strong> for AI/ML at Capital One,
        where I lead work on ML-powered fraud and spend management, and founder of
        <strong class="text-slate-900 dark:text-white font-semibold">Honeydew</strong>, an AI-powered family coordination app that uses voice, text,
        and photos to turn the day's loose ends into shared plans.
      </p>

      <p>
        Before that, I co-founded <strong class="text-slate-900 dark:text-white font-semibold">GiveTide</strong>, ran it for five years, and sold it in 2022.
        Building that company the expensive way is what made the new economics of AI-assisted software impossible for me to ignore.
      </p>

      <div class="border-l-2 border-(--color-primary) pl-6 py-2 my-8">
        <p class="text-slate-900 dark:text-white font-medium italic text-lg">
          "Intelligence became abundant. Intention did not."
        </p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white pt-4">The Questions I Keep Returning To</h2>

      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        {[
          { title: "Product Judgment", desc: "What should the system do, when should it ask, and what should it never guess?" },
          { title: "Evidence Over Demos", desc: "Real prompts, published methods, and the bad results beside the good ones." },
          { title: "Tools That Coordinate", desc: "How an agent chooses among 60+ tools without becoming reckless or useless." },
          { title: "Human Work", desc: "What gets more valuable when prose, code, and pattern recognition get cheap?" },
        ].map(item => (
          <div class="p-4 rounded-xl bg-slate-50 dark:bg-[#141b2d] border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-800">
            <p class="font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-1">{item.title}</p>
            <p class="text-sm">{item.desc}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>

      <h2 id="practice" class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white pt-4 scroll-mt-24">How I Sharpen the Craft</h2>

      <p>
        My practice loop is <strong class="text-slate-900 dark:text-white font-semibold">{PROFILE.practiceLoop.join(' → ')}</strong>.
        I start with a real operating problem, instrument the behavior, turn failures into evaluation cases, and revise the product before I write the conclusion.
      </p>

      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        {PROFILE.focusAreas.map(item => (
          <div class="p-4 rounded-xl bg-slate-50 dark:bg-[#141b2d] border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-800">
            <p class="font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-1">{item.title}</p>
            <p class="text-sm">{item.description}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-2 border-(--color-primary) pl-6 py-2 my-8">
        <p class="text-slate-900 dark:text-white font-medium">
          AI assists with research, red-teaming, implementation, and editing. I own the thesis, source selection, evaluation design, factual claims, and final editorial judgment.
        </p>
      </div>

      <p>
        That quality bar is visible in the work: methods and limitations sit beside results; corrections stay public; and a claim is narrowed when the evidence is thinner than the first draft suggested.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white pt-4">Background</h2>

      <p>
        I studied <strong class="text-slate-900 dark:text-white font-semibold">Finance & Economics</strong> at the
        <strong class="text-slate-900 dark:text-white font-semibold">University of Richmond</strong>, graduating Magna Cum Laude.
        My career has moved through fintech, fraud systems, consumer software, and the practical limits of AI agents.
        The through-line is less glamorous than “innovation”: take an ambiguous problem, make the tradeoffs explicit, and ship something people can trust.
      </p>

      <div class="mt-10 p-6 rounded-2xl bg-slate-50 dark:bg-[#141b2d] border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-800">
        <p class="font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-2">I write the work down.</p>
        <p class="text-sm mb-4">The essays range from model benchmarks to the parts of judgment a model cannot supply.</p>
        <a href="https://peterghiorse.substack.com/subscribe?utm_source=peterghiorse.com&utm_medium=website&utm_campaign=newsletter_growth&utm_content=about" target="_blank" rel="noopener" data-newsletter-cta data-newsletter-impression data-analytics-placement="about" class="text-(--color-primary) font-semibold hover:underline">Follow on Substack &rarr;</a>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-6 p-6 rounded-2xl border border-blue-200 dark:border-blue-900 bg-blue-50/70 dark:bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-2">For recruiters and hiring leaders</p>
        <p class="text-sm mb-4">{PROFILE.recruiterFocus}</p>
        <a href="/resume" data-profile-cta="recruiter_snapshot" data-analytics-placement="about" class="text-(--color-primary) font-semibold hover:underline">View the recruiter snapshot &rarr;</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
